cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method to improve facial recognition performance by rectifying facial geometry using local homography transformations. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions learning the rectification network and recognition network in an end-to-end manner. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method that uses AI techniques to improve facial recognition. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image rectification and recognition, which are related to multimedia processing. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper mentions using a regularization based on the natural face distribution, which could involve neural network techniques.
